WEBVTT

1
00:00:37.180 --> 00:00:40.020
I was sheriff of this county
when I was twenty five years old.

2
00:00:41.260 --> 00:00:42.620
Hard to believe.

3
00:00:43.500 --> 00:00:46.300
Grandfather was a lawman. Father too.

4
00:00:47.940 --> 00:00:51.980
Me and him was sheriff at the same
time. him up in Plano and me out here.

5
00:00:53.220 --> 00:00:54.540
I think he was pretty proud of that.

6
00:00:56.140 --> 00:00:56.940
I know I was.

7
00:00:58.860 --> 00:01:01.540
Some of the old-time sheriffs
never even wore a gun.

8
00:01:02.500 --> 00:01:04.500
A lot of folks find that hard to believe.

9
00:01:04.535 --> 00:01:06.140
Jim Scarborough never carried one.

10
00:01:06.175 --> 00:01:07.220
That the younger Jim.

11
00:01:07.900 --> 00:01:10.780
Gaston Boykins wouldn't wear
one up in Commanche County.

12
00:01:12.660 --> 00:01:14.900
Now I always liked to
hear about the old-timers.

13
00:01:16.180 --> 00:01:17.940
Never missed a chance to do so.

14
00:01:19.340 --> 00:01:22.340
You can't help but compare
yourself against the old-timers.

15
00:01:23.780 --> 00:01:26.220
Can't help but wonder how they
would've operated these times.

16
00:01:27.660 --> 00:01:31.420
There is this boy I sent to the electric
chair in Huntsville here a while back.

17
00:01:32.900 --> 00:01:35.340
My arrest and my testimony.

18
00:01:37.060 --> 00:01:39.260
He killed a
fourteen-year-old girl.

19
00:01:40.620 --> 00:01:45.580
Papers said it was a crime of passion but
he told me there wasn't any passion to it.

20
00:01:46.260 --> 00:01:50.500
Told me that he'd been planning to kill some-
body for about as long as he could remember.

21
00:01:50.535 --> 00:01:52.580
Said if they turned him out he'd do it again.

22
00:01:53.380 --> 00:01:54.580
Said he knew he was going to hell.

23
00:01:56.180 --> 00:01:57.620
Be there in about fifteen minutes.

24
00:01:58.660 --> 00:01:59.860
I don't know what to make of that.

25
00:02:01.260 --> 00:02:02.740
I surely don't.

26
00:02:05.260 --> 00:02:07.580
The crime you see now. it's
hard to even take its measure.

27
00:02:09.820 --> 00:02:11.420
It's not that I'm afraid of it.

28
00:02:13.380 --> 00:02:16.980
I always knew you had to be
willing to die to even do this job.

29
00:02:18.300 --> 00:02:20.860
But I don't want to push my chips forward...

30
00:02:21.660 --> 00:02:25.180
...and go out and meet
something I don't understand.

31
00:02:29.540 --> 00:02:31.980
A man would have to put his soul at hazard.

32
00:02:33.740 --> 00:02:35.700
He just have to say. okay.

33
00:02:40.420 --> 00:02:41.620
I'll be part of this world.

34
00:02:43.940 --> 00:02:45.740
Yes sir. I just walked in the door.

35
00:02:46.980 --> 00:02:49.540
Sheriff he had some sort
of thing on him like a...

36
00:02:49.580 --> 00:02:52.220
...oxygen tanks for emphysema or something.

37
00:02:52.660 --> 00:02:54.940
And a hose that run down his sleeve...

38
00:02:58.020 --> 00:02:58.705
You got me.

39
00:02:58.740 --> 00:03:00.660
You'll look at it when you get in.

40
00:03:00.820 --> 00:03:03.340
Yessir. I got it under control.

41
00:04:41.620 --> 00:04:43.545
Howdy. what's this about?

42
00:04:43.580 --> 00:04:45.060
Step out of the car please. sir.

43
00:04:45.780 --> 00:04:46.380
What is it?

44
00:04:47.340 --> 00:04:49.100
I need you to step out of the car. sir.

45
00:04:56.940 --> 00:04:58.140
What is that for?

46
00:04:59.460 --> 00:05:02.020
Would you hold still please. sir.

47
00:05:32.140 --> 00:05:33.060
Hold still.

48
00:09:14.540 --> 00:09:15.660
Agua.

49
00:09:18.060 --> 00:09:19.220
...Agua. Por Dios.

50
00:09:31.780 --> 00:09:32.740
Agua.

51
00:09:35.460 --> 00:09:37.020
I ain't got no water.

52
00:09:49.620 --> 00:09:50.580
Agua.

53
00:09:52.940 --> 00:09:54.140
I ain't got no agua.

54
00:10:09.500 --> 00:10:10.380
You speak English?

55
00:10:12.860 --> 00:10:14.220
Where's the last guy?

56
00:10:15.420 --> 00:10:16.345
Ultimo hombre.

57
00:10:16.380 --> 00:10:18.180
Last man standing. There must've been one.

58
00:10:18.215 --> 00:10:18.940
Where'd he go?

59
00:10:25.940 --> 00:10:28.060
I reckon I'd go out the way I came in.

60
00:10:29.260 --> 00:10:30.180
La puerta...

61
00:10:32.220 --> 00:10:33.220
Hay lobos...

62
00:10:34.820 --> 00:10:36.020
Ain't no lobos.

63
00:10:51.460 --> 00:10:57.460
If you stopped and watch your backtrack.
you're gonna shoot my dumb ass.

64
00:11:00.860 --> 00:11:05.500
But if you stopped. you stopped in the shade.

65
00:14:26.460 --> 00:14:27.900
What's in the satchel?

66
00:14:27.935 --> 00:14:29.340
It's full of money.

67
00:14:30.420 --> 00:14:31.500
That'll be the day.

68
00:14:32.980 --> 00:14:34.100
Where'd you get the pistol?

69
00:14:34.135 --> 00:14:35.420
At the gettin' place.

70
00:14:36.700 --> 00:14:37.940
Did you buy that gun?

71
00:14:38.140 --> 00:14:39.660
No. I found it.

72
00:14:42.020 --> 00:14:42.820
Welyn!

73
00:14:42.855 --> 00:14:43.585
What?

74
00:14:43.620 --> 00:14:44.700
Quit your hollering.

75
00:14:45.780 --> 00:14:47.260
What'd you give for that thing?

76
00:14:49.260 --> 00:14:51.140
You don't need to know everything. Carla Jean.

77
00:14:52.220 --> 00:14:53.540
I need to know that.

78
00:14:54.100 --> 00:14:57.700
You keep running that mouth of yours I'm
gonna take you in the back and screw you.

79
00:14:58.620 --> 00:14:59.700
Big talk.

80
00:15:00.060 --> 00:15:00.980
Keep it up.

81
00:15:01.660 --> 00:15:03.940
Fine. I don't wanna know.

82
00:15:05.100 --> 00:15:06.780
I don't even wanna know
where you been all day.

83
00:15:09.060 --> 00:15:09.980
That'll work.

84
00:15:24.780 --> 00:15:25.340
Alright.

85
00:15:32.060 --> 00:15:33.180
Llewelyn.

86
00:15:33.780 --> 00:15:34.540
Yeah?

87
00:15:36.980 --> 00:15:38.180
What're you doing. baby?

88
00:15:39.620 --> 00:15:40.300
I'm going out.

89
00:15:40.380 --> 00:15:41.420
Going where?

90
00:15:42.420 --> 00:15:44.660
Something I forgot to do but I'll be back.

91
00:15:45.900 --> 00:15:46.905
What're you going to do?

92
00:15:46.940 --> 00:15:50.620
I'm fixing to do something
dumber now but I'm going anyways.

93
00:15:53.220 --> 00:15:55.460
If I don't come back tell Mother I love her.

94
00:15:57.300 --> 00:15:58.660
Your mother's dead. Llewelyn.

95
00:16:03.020 --> 00:16:04.420
Well then. I'll tell her myself.

96
00:20:58.660 --> 00:20:59.500
How much?

97
00:20:59.700 --> 00:21:01.180
Sixty-nine cents.

98
00:21:01.580 --> 00:21:02.780
And the gas.

99
00:21:03.660 --> 00:21:05.740
Y'all getting any rain up your way?

100
00:21:07.380 --> 00:21:08.380
What way would that be?

101
00:21:08.460 --> 00:21:10.100
I seen you was from Dallas.

102
00:21:12.620 --> 00:21:18.220
What business is it of yours
where I'm from. friendo?

103
00:21:20.980 --> 00:21:22.380
I didn't mean nothing by it.

104
00:21:22.580 --> 00:21:23.900
Didn't mean nothing.

105
00:21:24.100 --> 00:21:26.380
Just passing my time.

106
00:21:28.740 --> 00:21:32.020
If you don't wanna accept that I
don't know what else I can do for you.

107
00:21:35.260 --> 00:21:36.620
Will there be something else?

108
00:21:36.655 --> 00:21:37.980
I don't know. Will there?

109
00:21:45.180 --> 00:21:46.220
Is somethin wrong?

110
00:21:46.255 --> 00:21:46.997
With what?

111
00:21:47.032 --> 00:21:47.740
With anything?

112
00:21:49.540 --> 00:21:50.780
Is that what you're asking me?

113
00:21:51.620 --> 00:21:53.340
Is there something wrong with anything?

114
00:21:54.220 --> 00:21:55.300
Will there be anything else?

115
00:21:55.340 --> 00:21:56.380
You already asked me that.

116
00:22:00.660 --> 00:22:02.580
Well... I need to see about closing.

117
00:22:03.020 --> 00:22:04.260
See about closing.

118
00:22:04.380 --> 00:22:04.825
Yessir.

119
00:22:04.860 --> 00:22:05.940
What time do you close?

120
00:22:05.975 --> 00:22:07.177
Now. We close now.

121
00:22:07.212 --> 00:22:08.345
Now is not a time.

122
00:22:08.380 --> 00:22:09.580
What time do you close?

123
00:22:09.620 --> 00:22:11.340
Generally around dark. At dark.

124
00:22:16.380 --> 00:22:18.180
You don't know what you're
talking about. do you?

125
00:22:18.215 --> 00:22:18.780
Sir?

126
00:22:21.020 --> 00:22:23.780
I said you don't know
what you're talking about.

127
00:22:26.860 --> 00:22:28.060
What time do you go to bed?

128
00:22:28.740 --> 00:22:29.260
Sir?

129
00:22:29.460 --> 00:22:31.180
You're a bit deaf. aren't you?

130
00:22:31.215 --> 00:22:32.900
I said what time do you go to bed?

131
00:22:37.500 --> 00:22:38.900
Somewhere around 9:30.

132
00:22:39.500 --> 00:22:41.080
I'd say around 9:30.

133
00:22:41.115 --> 00:22:42.625
I could come back then.

134
00:22:42.660 --> 00:22:43.980
Why would you be coming back?

135
00:22:44.015 --> 00:22:44.945
We'd be closed.

136
00:22:44.980 --> 00:22:45.980
Yeah. You said that.

137
00:22:48.340 --> 00:22:49.985
Well... I got to close now.

138
00:22:50.020 --> 00:22:51.580
You live in that house out back?

139
00:22:52.860 --> 00:22:54.700
Yes I do.

140
00:22:55.580 --> 00:22:57.020
You lived here all your life?

141
00:22:58.540 --> 00:23:02.420
This is my wife's father's place. Originally.

142
00:23:05.260 --> 00:23:06.140
You married into it.

143
00:23:06.860 --> 00:23:09.500
We lived in Temple Texas for many years.

144
00:23:10.980 --> 00:23:12.420
Raised a family there.

145
00:23:13.220 --> 00:23:14.425
In Temple.

146
00:23:14.460 --> 00:23:16.580
We come out here about four years ago.

147
00:23:17.540 --> 00:23:18.420
You married into it.

148
00:23:19.220 --> 00:23:20.700
If that's the way you wanna put it.

149
00:23:20.980 --> 00:23:22.660
I don't have some way to put it.

150
00:23:23.780 --> 00:23:24.860
That's the way it is.

151
00:23:33.220 --> 00:23:35.620
What's the most you've
ever lost in a coin toss?

152
00:23:36.980 --> 00:23:37.465
Sir?

153
00:23:37.500 --> 00:23:40.820
The most you ever lost in a coin toss.

154
00:23:42.980 --> 00:23:44.580
I don't know. I couldn't say.

155
00:23:47.700 --> 00:23:48.540
Call it.

156
00:23:49.300 --> 00:23:49.780
Call it?

157
00:23:49.900 --> 00:23:50.420
Yes.

158
00:23:51.060 --> 00:23:51.740
For what?

159
00:23:51.980 --> 00:23:52.780
Just call it.

160
00:23:55.900 --> 00:23:59.580
Well. we need to know what
we're calling it for here.

161
00:23:59.615 --> 00:24:00.620
You need to call it.

162
00:24:00.700 --> 00:24:02.380
I can't call it for you.

163
00:24:03.220 --> 00:24:04.460
It wouldn't be fair.

164
00:24:04.580 --> 00:24:06.140
I didn't put nothing up.

165
00:24:06.175 --> 00:24:07.420
Yes. you did.

166
00:24:08.060 --> 00:24:09.740
You've been putting it up your whole life.

167
00:24:09.775 --> 00:24:10.820
You just didn't know it.

168
00:24:12.100 --> 00:24:13.980
You know what date is on this coin?

169
00:24:14.260 --> 00:24:15.220
No.

170
00:24:15.260 --> 00:24:16.180
1958.

171
00:24:17.100 --> 00:24:19.300
It's been traveling
twenty-two years to get here.

172
00:24:19.820 --> 00:24:20.780
And now it's here.

173
00:24:21.940 --> 00:24:23.140
And it's either heads or tails.

174
00:24:24.660 --> 00:24:25.900
And you have to say. Call it.

175
00:24:26.180 --> 00:24:29.260
Look... I need to know what I stand to win.

176
00:24:29.660 --> 00:24:30.420
Everything.

177
00:24:31.780 --> 00:24:32.265
How's that?

178
00:24:32.300 --> 00:24:34.460
You stand to win everything. Call it.

179
00:24:39.260 --> 00:24:42.380
Alright. Heads then.

180
00:24:47.140 --> 00:24:48.060
Well done.

181
00:24:50.580 --> 00:24:51.380
Don't put it in your pocket.

182
00:24:51.500 --> 00:24:52.385
Sir?

183
00:24:52.420 --> 00:24:54.460
Don't put it in your pocket.
It's your lucky quarter.

184
00:24:56.740 --> 00:24:57.860
Where you want me to put it?

185
00:24:57.895 --> 00:24:58.980
Anywhere not in your pocket.

186
00:25:00.220 --> 00:25:03.300
Or it'll be mixed in with the
others and become just a coin.

187
00:25:07.780 --> 00:25:08.340
Which it is.

188
00:25:20.380 --> 00:25:21.180
Llewelyn?

189
00:25:24.300 --> 00:25:25.060
What the hell?

190
00:25:27.460 --> 00:25:28.140
Odessa.

191
00:25:28.700 --> 00:25:30.340
Why would we go to Odessa?

192
00:25:30.660 --> 00:25:33.300
Not we. you. Stay with your mother.

193
00:25:34.140 --> 00:25:34.980
Well. how come?

194
00:25:35.700 --> 00:25:37.345
Right now it's midnight Sunday.

195
00:25:37.380 --> 00:25:39.545
When the courthouse opens
nine hours from now...

196
00:25:39.580 --> 00:25:42.980
...someone's gonna be callin' in the vehicle
number on the inspection plate on the truck.

197
00:25:43.620 --> 00:25:45.460
And by 9:30. they'll show up here.

198
00:25:46.060 --> 00:25:47.465
But for how long do we have to...

199
00:25:47.500 --> 00:25:50.740
Baby. at what point would you quit bothering
to look for your two million dollars?

200
00:25:52.140 --> 00:25:53.540
What am I supposed to tell Mama?

201
00:25:54.500 --> 00:25:57.020
Try standin' in the door
and holler "Mama. I'm home".

202
00:25:57.055 --> 00:25:57.785
Llewelyn...

203
00:25:57.820 --> 00:25:58.705
C'mon. pack your things.

204
00:25:58.740 --> 00:26:01.380
Anything you leave you
ain't gonna see it again.

205
00:26:03.660 --> 00:26:07.100
Well. thanks for falling
all over and apologizing.

206
00:26:07.820 --> 00:26:11.940
Baby. things happened. I can't take 'em back.

207
00:26:35.380 --> 00:26:36.540
Mind ridin'. bitch?

208
00:26:50.180 --> 00:26:50.900
This his truck?

209
00:26:51.380 --> 00:26:51.940
Mm-Mm.

210
00:26:56.340 --> 00:26:57.300
Got a screwgie?

211
00:27:01.260 --> 00:27:02.505
Who cut his tires?

212
00:27:02.540 --> 00:27:05.180
Mexicans. I guess. Wasn't us.

213
00:27:06.580 --> 00:27:08.020
That's a dead dog.

214
00:27:08.220 --> 00:27:09.180
Yes. it is.

215
00:27:13.340 --> 00:27:14.300
Where's the receiver?

216
00:27:14.500 --> 00:27:15.460
I've got it.

217
00:27:17.620 --> 00:27:18.580
They're ripe petunias.

218
00:27:20.180 --> 00:27:21.460
Hold this please.

219
00:27:29.780 --> 00:27:30.980
You want it?

220
00:27:33.500 --> 00:27:34.660
You getting anything though?

221
00:27:35.420 --> 00:27:36.460
Not a bleep.

222
00:27:37.700 --> 00:27:38.620
Alright...

223
00:27:42.020 --> 00:27:42.820
Gimme that.

224
00:27:53.300 --> 00:27:55.300
I thought it was a car afire.

225
00:27:55.335 --> 00:27:56.265
It is a car afire.

226
00:27:56.300 --> 00:27:58.580
But Wnedell said there was
something backcountry too.

227
00:28:01.060 --> 00:28:03.900
When is the county gonna start
paying a rental on my horse?

228
00:28:03.935 --> 00:28:05.380
I love you more and more everyday.

229
00:28:05.660 --> 00:28:06.780
That's very nice.

230
00:28:08.460 --> 00:28:09.040
Be careful.

231
00:28:09.075 --> 00:28:09.620
Always am.

232
00:28:10.180 --> 00:28:10.820
Don't get hurt.

233
00:28:10.855 --> 00:28:11.620
Never do.

234
00:28:11.860 --> 00:28:12.980
Don't hurt no one.

235
00:28:16.140 --> 00:28:17.060
If you say so.

236
00:28:52.140 --> 00:28:54.740
Wouldn't think a car would burn like that.

237
00:28:54.860 --> 00:28:58.265
Yessir. We should've brought weenies.

238
00:28:58.300 --> 00:29:00.900
That look like about a
'77 Ford to you. Wendell?

239
00:29:01.260 --> 00:29:02.305
It could be.

240
00:29:02.340 --> 00:29:04.380
I'd say it is. Not a doubt in my mind.

241
00:29:04.620 --> 00:29:06.260
The old boy shot by the highway?

242
00:29:06.295 --> 00:29:08.620
Yessir. his vehicle.

243
00:29:09.740 --> 00:29:12.300
Man killed Lamar's deputy and took his car.

244
00:29:12.335 --> 00:29:13.740
Killed that man on the highway...

245
00:29:13.775 --> 00:29:15.065
...swapped for his car...

246
00:29:15.100 --> 00:29:18.540
...and now here it is and he's
swapped again for god knows what.

247
00:29:19.540 --> 00:29:22.500
That's very linear. Sheriff.

248
00:29:22.860 --> 00:29:24.545
Well. Old age flattens a man.

249
00:29:24.580 --> 00:29:28.220
Yessir. But then there's this other.

250
00:29:30.260 --> 00:29:31.860
You ride Winston.

251
00:29:32.100 --> 00:29:34.140
- You sure?
- Oh. I'm more than sure.

252
00:29:35.060 --> 00:29:36.825
Anything happens to
Loretta's horse out here...

253
00:29:36.860 --> 00:29:39.820
...I can tell you right now I don't
wanna be the party that was aboard.

254
00:29:41.140 --> 00:29:43.900
It's the same tire tread comin back as going.

255
00:29:43.980 --> 00:29:47.300
Made about the same time too.
You can see the sipes real clear.

256
00:29:49.620 --> 00:29:52.580
Somebodies pried the inspection
plate off the door on this one.

257
00:29:54.660 --> 00:29:57.020
I know this truck.

258
00:29:57.380 --> 00:29:59.500
Belongs to a fella named Moss.

259
00:29:59.860 --> 00:30:02.180
- Llewelyn Moss?
- That's the boy.

260
00:30:02.820 --> 00:30:05.540
You figure him for a doperunner?

261
00:30:05.575 --> 00:30:08.260
I don't know but I kindly doubt it.

262
00:30:08.420 --> 00:30:10.540
Restul sunt acolo.

263
00:30:12.820 --> 00:30:14.980
Oh hell's bells. they even shot the dog.

264
00:30:18.700 --> 00:30:21.700
Well this is just a deal gone wrong. isn't it?

265
00:30:21.735 --> 00:30:24.700
Yeah. appears to have been a glitch or two.

266
00:30:28.660 --> 00:30:31.800
What calibers you got there. Sheriff?

267
00:30:31.835 --> 00:30:34.940
Nine millimeter. Couple of .45 ACP's.

268
00:30:36.380 --> 00:30:39.620
Somebody unloaded on
that thing with a shotgun.

269
00:30:42.060 --> 00:30:44.380
How come do you reckon the
coyotes ain't been at 'em?

270
00:30:44.415 --> 00:30:46.220
I don't know.

271
00:30:51.380 --> 00:30:54.180
Supposedly coyotes won't eat a Mexican.

272
00:30:54.420 --> 00:30:57.100
These boys appear to be managerial.

273
00:30:57.580 --> 00:30:59.980
I think we're lookin at
more than one fracas...

274
00:31:00.015 --> 00:31:01.465
Execution here...

275
00:31:01.500 --> 00:31:03.420
...Wild West over there

276
00:31:04.700 --> 00:31:06.840
That Mexican brown dope.

277
00:31:06.875 --> 00:31:08.945
These boys is all swole up.

278
00:31:08.980 --> 00:31:11.940
So this was earlier. getting set to trade.

279
00:31:11.980 --> 00:31:14.420
Then. whoa. differences...

280
00:31:15.140 --> 00:31:17.100
You know might not of even been no money.

281
00:31:17.140 --> 00:31:18.620
That's possible.

282
00:31:19.060 --> 00:31:20.460
But you don't believe it.

283
00:31:21.100 --> 00:31:23.980
No. Probably I don't.

284
00:31:26.940 --> 00:31:29.300
Well. it's a mess. ain't it Sheriff?

285
00:31:31.500 --> 00:31:34.900
If it ain't. it'll do till a mess gets here.

286
00:33:28.300 --> 00:33:29.180
Yessir?

287
00:33:30.580 --> 00:33:32.180
I'm looking for Llewelyn Moss.

288
00:33:32.540 --> 00:33:34.300
Did you go up to his trailer?

289
00:33:34.660 --> 00:33:35.140
Yes.

290
00:33:35.740 --> 00:33:38.980
Well. I'd say he's at work.
Do you want to leave a message?

291
00:33:39.100 --> 00:33:40.100
Where does he work?

292
00:33:40.620 --> 00:33:41.700
I can't say.

293
00:33:44.340 --> 00:33:45.545
Where does he work?

294
00:33:45.580 --> 00:33:50.020
Sir. I ain't at liberty to give out
no information about our residents.

295
00:33:51.020 --> 00:33:52.825
Where does he work?

296
00:33:52.860 --> 00:33:58.340
Did you not hear me? We
can't give out no information.

297
00:34:20.900 --> 00:34:22.505
Why all the way to Del Rio?

298
00:34:22.540 --> 00:34:24.900
I'm gonna borrow a car from Roberto.

299
00:34:24.980 --> 00:34:26.500
You can't afford one?

300
00:34:27.460 --> 00:34:28.945
I don't wanna register it.

301
00:34:28.980 --> 00:34:30.780
Look. I'll call you in a couple days.

302
00:34:30.815 --> 00:34:32.860
- Promise?
- Yes. I do.

303
00:34:33.940 --> 00:34:35.825
I got a bad feeling. Llewelyn.

304
00:34:35.860 --> 00:34:38.380
Well I got a good one.
So. they ought to even out.

305
00:34:39.100 --> 00:34:41.740
Quit worrying so much.

306
00:34:42.300 --> 00:34:43.740
Mama's gonna raise hell.

307
00:34:44.540 --> 00:34:46.340
She is just gonna curse you up and down.

308
00:34:46.375 --> 00:34:48.305
You should be used to that.

309
00:34:48.340 --> 00:34:51.260
I'm used to lots of
things. I work at Wal-Mart.

310
00:34:51.460 --> 00:34:54.740
Not any more. Carla Jean. You're retired.

311
00:34:55.020 --> 00:34:57.460
- Llewelyn?
- Yes ma'am?

312
00:34:59.140 --> 00:35:04.140
- You are comin back. ain't ya?
- I shall return.

313
00:35:08.980 --> 00:35:10.900
Sheriff's Department!

314
00:35:12.900 --> 00:35:14.500
Look at that lock.

315
00:35:17.300 --> 00:35:18.680
We goin' in?

316
00:35:18.715 --> 00:35:20.060
Gun out and up.

317
00:35:23.580 --> 00:35:26.780
- What about yours?
- I'm hidin behind you.

318
00:35:29.740 --> 00:35:31.540
Sheriff's Department!

319
00:35:57.780 --> 00:35:59.660
I believe they've lit a shuck.

320
00:35:59.695 --> 00:36:01.137
I believe you're right.

321
00:36:01.172 --> 00:36:02.580
That from the lock?

322
00:36:02.860 --> 00:36:04.620
Probably must be.

323
00:36:04.820 --> 00:36:06.260
When was he here. Sheriff?

324
00:36:06.295 --> 00:36:06.985
I don't know.

325
00:36:07.020 --> 00:36:10.180
Oh. Now that's aggravating.

326
00:36:10.340 --> 00:36:11.185
Sheriff?

327
00:36:11.220 --> 00:36:12.780
Still sweating.

328
00:36:12.940 --> 00:36:16.580
Oh. Sheriff. we just missed him!

329
00:36:17.980 --> 00:36:20.700
We gotta circulate this. On radio.

330
00:36:21.540 --> 00:36:22.740
Alright.

331
00:36:23.780 --> 00:36:25.820
What do we circulate?

332
00:36:28.180 --> 00:36:31.380
Lookin for a man who has recently drunk milk?

333
00:36:34.620 --> 00:36:37.220
Ah. Sheriff. that's aggravating.

334
00:36:37.255 --> 00:36:39.380
I'm ahead of you there.

335
00:36:41.260 --> 00:36:46.100
You think this boy Moss has got any notion of
the sorts of sons of bitches that are hunting him?

336
00:36:46.135 --> 00:36:48.260
I don't know. He ought to...

337
00:36:51.100 --> 00:36:53.385
He seen the same things I've seen...

338
00:36:53.420 --> 00:36:56.500
...and it certainly made an impression on me.

339
00:37:02.500 --> 00:37:04.460
- Take me to a motel.
- Got one in mind?

340
00:37:04.495 --> 00:37:06.100
Someplace cheap.

341
00:37:08.100 --> 00:37:10.180
You tell me the option.

342
00:37:10.215 --> 00:37:11.505
Do what now?

343
00:37:11.540 --> 00:37:15.220
You pick the option goes
with the applicable rate.

344
00:37:17.060 --> 00:37:20.060
I'm just one person. So. don't
matter the size of the bed.

345
00:37:26.260 --> 00:37:29.140
<i>This is Roberto Sagramore.
I'm not here right now.</i>

346
00:37:29.175 --> 00:37:30.540
<i>Please leave a message.</i>

347
00:39:29.860 --> 00:39:31.140
Hello?

348
00:39:31.900 --> 00:39:33.620
Is Llewelyn there?

349
00:39:33.900 --> 00:39:36.620
Llewelyn?! No he ain't.

350
00:39:37.500 --> 00:39:39.105
You expect him?

351
00:39:39.140 --> 00:39:41.060
Now why would I expect him?

352
00:39:41.420 --> 00:39:43.260
Who's this?

353
00:39:51.260 --> 00:39:52.385
Can I help you?

354
00:39:52.420 --> 00:39:55.620
Yeah. You got a pair of Larry
Mahan's. shoulder size 11.

355
00:39:55.655 --> 00:39:57.025
I'll check.

356
00:39:57.060 --> 00:39:58.980
- You sell socks?
- Just white.

357
00:39:59.020 --> 00:40:00.820
White is all I wear.

358
00:40:01.060 --> 00:40:02.620
You got a bathroom?

359
00:40:28.100 --> 00:40:31.620
Don't stop. Just ride me up past those rooms.

360
00:40:31.740 --> 00:40:34.980
- What room?
- Just drive me around.

361
00:40:35.420 --> 00:40:37.220
I want to see if someone's here.

362
00:40:45.220 --> 00:40:46.860
Keep going. Don't stop.

363
00:40:47.300 --> 00:40:50.180
I don't wanna get into some
kind of a jackpot here. buddy.

364
00:40:50.215 --> 00:40:51.540
It's alright.

365
00:40:52.340 --> 00:40:55.340
Why don't I just set you down around
here and we won't argue about it.

366
00:40:56.260 --> 00:40:57.940
Take me to another motel.

367
00:40:58.060 --> 00:40:59.425
Let's just call it square.

368
00:40:59.460 --> 00:41:02.460
Look. you're already in a jackpot.
I'm trying to get you out of it.

369
00:41:02.495 --> 00:41:04.140
Now take me to another motel.

370
00:41:53.740 --> 00:41:56.260
The lab reports from Austin
on that boy by the highway.

371
00:41:56.295 --> 00:41:57.597
What was the bullet?

372
00:41:57.632 --> 00:41:58.900
There wasn't no bullet.

373
00:42:00.020 --> 00:42:01.500
Wasn't no bullet?

374
00:42:01.535 --> 00:42:02.980
Yessir. Wasn't none.

375
00:42:03.540 --> 00:42:08.220
Well. Wendell. with all due respect.
that don't make a lot of sense.

376
00:42:08.580 --> 00:42:09.860
No sir.

377
00:42:09.900 --> 00:42:12.660
You said entry wound in the forehead.

378
00:42:12.695 --> 00:42:14.020
No exit wound.

379
00:42:14.055 --> 00:42:14.825
Yes sir.

380
00:42:14.860 --> 00:42:16.705
Are you telling he shot
this boy in the head...

381
00:42:16.740 --> 00:42:18.860
...and then went digging around
in there with a pocket knife?

382
00:42:19.940 --> 00:42:21.900
Sir. I don't want to picture that.

383
00:42:21.935 --> 00:42:23.305
I don't either!

384
00:42:23.340 --> 00:42:25.180
Can I freshen that there for you. Sheriff?

385
00:42:25.500 --> 00:42:27.740
Yeah. Noreen. you better had.

386
00:42:28.180 --> 00:42:31.220
The Rangers and the DEA are headed
back out to the scene this morning.

387
00:42:31.540 --> 00:42:33.460
You gonna join 'em?

388
00:42:34.060 --> 00:42:35.940
Any new bodies accumulated out there?

389
00:42:37.580 --> 00:42:38.860
No sir.

390
00:42:38.940 --> 00:42:40.860
Well then. I guess I can skip it.

391
00:42:55.540 --> 00:42:57.785
Twelve gauge. You need shells?

392
00:42:57.820 --> 00:43:01.820
- Yeah. Double ought.
- They'll give you a wallop.

393
00:43:01.980 --> 00:43:03.780
Y'all got camping supplies?

394
00:43:03.815 --> 00:43:05.865
Tent poles?

395
00:43:05.900 --> 00:43:07.360
You already have a tent?

396
00:43:07.395 --> 00:43:08.785
Somethin' like that.

397
00:43:08.820 --> 00:43:11.580
Well. you give me the model number on
the tent. I can order you the poles.

398
00:43:11.620 --> 00:43:13.105
Never mind. I want a tent.

399
00:43:13.140 --> 00:43:16.460
- Well. what kind of tent?
- The kind with the most poles.

400
00:43:38.940 --> 00:43:40.300
Could I get another room?

401
00:43:40.335 --> 00:43:41.625
You want to change rooms?

402
00:43:41.660 --> 00:43:44.140
No m'am. I want to keep my
room and get another one.

403
00:43:44.175 --> 00:43:45.540
Another additional?

404
00:43:45.575 --> 00:43:46.785
Yes. m'am.

405
00:43:46.820 --> 00:43:49.020
And do you have a map of the rooms?

406
00:43:49.055 --> 00:43:52.140
Yeah. we had a sorta one.

407
00:43:59.580 --> 00:44:01.180
How bout 38?

408
00:44:01.260 --> 00:44:04.140
Well. you can have the one
right next to yours if you want.

409
00:44:04.175 --> 00:44:06.060
Number 137. It ain't took.

410
00:44:06.095 --> 00:44:07.740
No. 38 will be fine.

411
00:44:08.100 --> 00:44:10.220
That's got two double beds.

412
00:50:38.060 --> 00:50:39.580
No me. mate.

413
00:50:45.620 --> 00:50:47.500
How'd you find it?

414
00:50:48.060 --> 00:50:50.140
No me. mate.

415
00:52:34.380 --> 00:52:39.180
Shouldn't be doin' that.
Even a young man like you.

416
00:52:40.820 --> 00:52:44.900
- Doin what?
- Hitchhiking.

417
00:52:50.260 --> 00:52:52.300
Dangerous.

418
00:53:10.220 --> 00:53:13.580
You know Anton Chigurh
by sight. is that correct?

419
00:53:13.615 --> 00:53:16.220
Yessir.

420
00:53:17.180 --> 00:53:18.900
When did you last see him?

421
00:53:21.140 --> 00:53:23.740
November 28th. last year.

422
00:53:24.860 --> 00:53:28.340
You seem pretty sure of the
date. Did I ask you to sit?

423
00:53:28.375 --> 00:53:29.025
No sir.

424
00:53:29.060 --> 00:53:33.340
But you struck me as a man who
wouldn't want to waste a chair.

425
00:53:33.375 --> 00:53:37.620
I remember dates. Names. Numbers.
I saw him November the 28th.

426
00:53:40.300 --> 00:53:42.185
We got a loose cannon here.

427
00:53:42.220 --> 00:53:43.505
And we're out a bunch of money...

428
00:53:43.540 --> 00:53:45.460
...and the other party is out his product.

429
00:53:45.495 --> 00:53:46.425
Yessir.

430
00:53:46.460 --> 00:53:51.420
This account will give up twelve hundred
dollars in any twenty-four hour period.

431
00:53:51.455 --> 00:53:53.500
That's up from a thousand.

432
00:53:53.620 --> 00:53:56.260
If your expenses run higher
I hope you'll trust us for it.

433
00:53:57.100 --> 00:53:58.620
Okay.

434
00:53:59.380 --> 00:54:01.860
Just how well do you know Chigurh?

435
00:54:02.180 --> 00:54:03.265
What do you want to know?

436
00:54:03.300 --> 00:54:05.780
I just want to know your opinion of him.

437
00:54:05.815 --> 00:54:06.700
In general.

438
00:54:07.140 --> 00:54:09.620
Just how dangerous is he?

439
00:54:09.660 --> 00:54:12.580
Compared to what? The bubonic plague?

440
00:54:12.700 --> 00:54:14.820
He's bad enough that you called me.

441
00:54:14.900 --> 00:54:18.540
Yeah. he's a psychopathic killer but so what?

442
00:54:19.540 --> 00:54:21.020
There's plenty of them around.

443
00:54:21.260 --> 00:54:23.865
He killed three men in
Del Rio Motel yesterday.

444
00:54:23.900 --> 00:54:27.660
And two others in that colossal
goatfuck out in the desert.

445
00:54:28.020 --> 00:54:29.385
We can stop that.

446
00:54:29.420 --> 00:54:31.140
You seem pretty sure of yourself.

447
00:54:32.900 --> 00:54:36.860
You've led something of a charmed
life haven't you. Mr. Wells?

448
00:54:37.380 --> 00:54:38.785
In all honesty...

449
00:54:38.820 --> 00:54:42.500
...I can't say that charm has
had a whole lot to do with it.

450
00:54:44.380 --> 00:54:45.820
I'm wondering...

451
00:54:45.860 --> 00:54:47.260
Yes?

452
00:54:48.020 --> 00:54:50.500
Can I get my parking ticket validated?

453
00:54:52.580 --> 00:54:55.380
An attempt at humor. I suppose.

454
00:54:55.420 --> 00:54:56.940
I'm sorry.

455
00:55:01.380 --> 00:55:07.340
You know I counted the floors
of this building from the street?

456
00:55:07.700 --> 00:55:09.820
There's one missing.

457
00:55:12.220 --> 00:55:14.220
We'll look into it.

458
00:55:33.900 --> 00:55:36.580
One room. one night.

459
00:55:36.940 --> 00:55:40.140
- That'll be twenty-six
dollars. - Alright.

460
00:55:44.500 --> 00:55:45.985
You on all night?

461
00:55:46.020 --> 00:55:49.020
Yessir. I'll be around here
until ten o'clock in the morning.

462
00:55:50.940 --> 00:55:54.580
This here's for you. Now. I ain't
asking you to do anything illegal.

463
00:55:55.380 --> 00:55:57.660
There's someone who's been
lookin for me. Not police.

464
00:55:57.695 --> 00:56:01.180
Just call me if anyone else checks in tonight.

465
00:56:01.300 --> 00:56:04.020
By anyone. I mean any swinging dude.

466
00:56:45.600 --> 00:56:47.820
There just ain't no way.

467
01:02:25.580 --> 01:02:27.420
Don't worry. I ain't gonna hurt you.

468
01:02:28.220 --> 01:02:30.220
I need you to drive me on out of here.

469
01:06:15.940 --> 01:06:17.380
Were you in a car accident?

470
01:06:18.620 --> 01:06:19.700
Yeah.

471
01:06:21.100 --> 01:06:23.780
- Gimme the money.
- It's right here. Give me the clothes.

472
01:06:24.100 --> 01:06:26.300
Let him hold the money.

473
01:06:41.900 --> 01:06:43.620
Gimme that beer too.

474
01:06:45.940 --> 01:06:47.260
How much?

475
01:06:48.420 --> 01:06:50.180
Brian. Give him the beer.

476
01:09:02.060 --> 01:09:06.180
Medico. Por favor.

477
01:13:10.420 --> 01:13:12.060
Any word on those vehicles yet?

478
01:13:12.780 --> 01:13:15.100
Sheriff. I found out
everything there was to find.

479
01:13:15.740 --> 01:13:18.900
Those vehicles are titled and
registered to deceased people.

480
01:13:20.300 --> 01:13:22.700
The owner of that Bronco's
been dead twenty years.

481
01:13:22.940 --> 01:13:25.060
Did you want me to see what I could
find out about the Mexican ones?

482
01:13:25.500 --> 01:13:27.060
No. Lord no.

483
01:13:27.940 --> 01:13:29.700
Here's this month's checks.

484
01:13:31.020 --> 01:13:32.560
That DEA agent called again.

485
01:13:32.595 --> 01:13:34.065
You don't want to talk to him?

486
01:13:34.100 --> 01:13:36.260
I'm goin' to try and keep
from it as much as I can.

487
01:13:36.580 --> 01:13:39.620
He's goin' back out there and he wanted
to know if you wanted to go with him.

488
01:13:39.660 --> 01:13:41.380
That's cordial of him.

489
01:13:42.180 --> 01:13:44.425
Could I get you to call Loretta for me...

490
01:13:44.460 --> 01:13:46.740
...and tell her I'm goin' to
Odessa to see Carla Jean Moss?

491
01:13:46.780 --> 01:13:48.220
Yes. Sheriff.

492
01:13:48.260 --> 01:13:50.420
I'll call her when I get there.

493
01:13:50.460 --> 01:13:53.220
I'd call her now but she'll want
me to come home and I just might.

494
01:13:53.260 --> 01:13:56.180
You want me to wait til
you've quit the building?

495
01:13:56.820 --> 01:14:00.100
You don't want to lie without
what it's absolutely necessary.

496
01:14:03.300 --> 01:14:06.220
What is it that Torbert
says about truth and justice?

497
01:14:06.980 --> 01:14:10.780
Oh. we dedicate ourselves
daily anew. Something like that.

498
01:14:10.820 --> 01:14:13.660
I think I'm goin' to commence
dedicatin' myself twice daily.

499
01:14:13.700 --> 01:14:16.460
It might come to three
times before it's over...

500
01:14:17.860 --> 01:14:19.420
Oh. what the hell?

501
01:14:27.940 --> 01:14:29.260
Sheriff?

502
01:14:30.740 --> 01:14:31.700
Have you looked at your load lately?

503
01:14:34.020 --> 01:14:35.060
That is a damned outrage.

504
01:14:36.420 --> 01:14:38.300
Oh. One of those tiedowns worked lose.

505
01:14:38.540 --> 01:14:39.940
How many bodies did you leave with?

506
01:14:40.500 --> 01:14:42.220
I ain't lost none of 'em. Sheriff.

507
01:14:43.540 --> 01:14:45.780
Couldn't you all of took a van out there?

508
01:14:46.220 --> 01:14:48.340
Didn't have no van with four-wheel drive.

509
01:14:48.580 --> 01:14:51.060
You going to write me up
for improperly secured load?

510
01:14:51.100 --> 01:14:52.740
You get your ass out of here.

511
01:14:59.980 --> 01:15:02.860
I'm guessin' this isn't the future
you had pictured for yourself...

512
01:15:02.900 --> 01:15:05.780
...when you first clapped eyes on that money.

513
01:15:06.420 --> 01:15:09.780
Don't worry. I'm not the man that's after you.

514
01:15:10.380 --> 01:15:11.780
I know.

515
01:15:13.660 --> 01:15:16.420
- I've seen him.
- You've seen him?

516
01:15:16.700 --> 01:15:18.500
And you're not dead.

517
01:15:20.660 --> 01:15:23.500
Is this guy supposed to
be the ultimate bad-ass?

518
01:15:23.740 --> 01:15:27.060
- I don't think that's how I'd describe him.
- How would you describe him?

519
01:15:28.380 --> 01:15:31.580
I guess I'd say... he
doesn't have a sense of humor.

520
01:15:32.020 --> 01:15:33.700
His name is Chigurh.

521
01:15:33.740 --> 01:15:36.380
- Sugar?
- Chigurh. Anton Chigurh.

522
01:15:37.100 --> 01:15:40.180
- You know how he found you?
- I know how he found me.

523
01:15:40.220 --> 01:15:42.980
- It's called a transponder.
- I know what it is.

524
01:15:43.500 --> 01:15:45.220
He won't find me again.

525
01:15:45.540 --> 01:15:47.540
- Not that way.
- Not any way.

526
01:15:47.580 --> 01:15:51.100
- Took me about three hours.
- Yeah. well. I've been immobile.

527
01:15:52.020 --> 01:15:54.540
No. You don't understand.

528
01:15:56.260 --> 01:15:59.820
- What do you do?
- I'm retired.

529
01:16:00.020 --> 01:16:01.500
What did you do?

530
01:16:01.540 --> 01:16:03.780
- Welder.
- Acetylene? Mig? Tig?

531
01:16:03.820 --> 01:16:06.260
Any of it. If it can be welded. I can weld it.

532
01:16:06.300 --> 01:16:08.185
- Cast iron?
- Yes.

533
01:16:08.220 --> 01:16:10.540
- I don't mean braze.
- I didn't say braze.

534
01:16:10.580 --> 01:16:12.740
- Pot metal?
- What did I say?

535
01:16:14.340 --> 01:16:16.020
Were you in Nam?

536
01:16:17.460 --> 01:16:19.100
Yeah. I was in Nam.

537
01:16:20.860 --> 01:16:22.700
So was I.

538
01:16:23.060 --> 01:16:25.340
So what does that make me. your buddy?

539
01:16:27.260 --> 01:16:31.740
Look. you gotta give me this money.
I got no other reason to protect you.

540
01:16:32.980 --> 01:16:35.300
It's too late. I spent it.

541
01:16:37.100 --> 01:16:41.020
About a million and a half on whores and whiskey
...and the rest of it. I just sort of blew it here.

542
01:16:43.980 --> 01:16:46.660
How do you know he's not on his way to Odessa?

543
01:16:50.580 --> 01:16:54.660
- Why would he go to Odessa?
- To kill your wife.

544
01:17:01.860 --> 01:17:03.940
Maybe he's the one who needs to be worried.

545
01:17:05.140 --> 01:17:07.420
- About me.
- He isn't.

546
01:17:09.580 --> 01:17:11.540
You're not cut out for this.

547
01:17:12.180 --> 01:17:16.100
You're just a guy who happened
to find those vehicles.

548
01:17:21.300 --> 01:17:25.820
I'm across the river. At the
Hotel Eagle. Carson Wells.

549
01:17:26.980 --> 01:17:29.140
Call me when you've had enough.

550
01:17:29.380 --> 01:17:31.860
I can even let you keep a little of the money.

551
01:17:32.220 --> 01:17:33.305
If I was into cutting deals...

552
01:17:33.340 --> 01:17:35.620
...why wouldn't I just
deal with this guy Chigurh?

553
01:17:36.340 --> 01:17:39.940
You don't understand. You
can't make a deal with him.

554
01:17:40.260 --> 01:17:42.780
Even if you gave him the money
back. he'd still kill you...

555
01:17:42.815 --> 01:17:45.300
...just for inconvenience in him.

556
01:17:45.580 --> 01:17:49.260
He's a peculiar man. Might
even say he has principles.

557
01:17:49.540 --> 01:17:54.340
Principles that transcend money
or drugs or anything like that.

558
01:17:54.820 --> 01:17:59.380
He's not like you. He's not even like me.

559
01:18:00.220 --> 01:18:03.860
He don't talk as much as you.
I give him points for that.

560
01:18:05.700 --> 01:18:07.860
Carla Jean. Thank you for comin'.

561
01:18:07.900 --> 01:18:09.300
Don't know why I did.

562
01:18:09.980 --> 01:18:12.860
I told you. I don't know where he is.

563
01:18:13.100 --> 01:18:15.140
- You ain't heard from him?
- No I ain't.

564
01:18:15.180 --> 01:18:17.060
- Nothin'?
- Not word one.

565
01:18:17.260 --> 01:18:21.180
- Would you tell me if you had?
- Well. I don't know.

566
01:18:22.140 --> 01:18:25.460
- He don't need any trouble from you.
- It ain't me he's in trouble with.

567
01:18:26.260 --> 01:18:29.460
- Who's he in trouble with then?
- Some pretty bad people.

568
01:18:30.460 --> 01:18:33.740
These people will kill him.
Carla Jean. They won't quit.

569
01:18:34.020 --> 01:18:36.940
He won't neither. He never has.

570
01:18:37.580 --> 01:18:39.780
He can take all comers.

571
01:18:42.460 --> 01:18:45.900
You know Charlie Walser? He's got
that place out east of Sanderson?

572
01:18:49.100 --> 01:18:52.220
Well you know how they used to slaughter
beefs. hit 'em right there with a maul...

573
01:18:52.260 --> 01:18:54.020
.. truss 'em up and slit their throats?

574
01:18:54.500 --> 01:18:57.220
Here Charlie's got one all trussed
up and all set to drain him...

575
01:18:57.260 --> 01:18:59.620
...and the beef comes to.
It starts thrashing around.

576
01:19:00.660 --> 01:19:04.820
Six hundred pounds of very pissed-off
livestock if you'll excuse me.

577
01:19:05.820 --> 01:19:08.500
Charlie grabs his gun there to
shoot the damn thing in the head...

578
01:19:08.900 --> 01:19:14.300
...but with all the swayin' and then the trashin' it's a glance-shot
and ricochets around and comes back hits Charlie in the shoulder.

579
01:19:14.340 --> 01:19:15.505
You go see Charlie...

580
01:19:15.540 --> 01:19:18.020
he still can't pick up his
right hand for his hat...

581
01:19:18.580 --> 01:19:21.700
The point bein'. even in the
contest between man and steer...

582
01:19:21.735 --> 01:19:24.220
...the issue is not certain.

583
01:19:31.940 --> 01:19:36.660
When Llewelyn calls. just
tell him I'll make him safe.

584
01:19:41.460 --> 01:19:44.100
Course they slaughter steers
a lot different these days.

585
01:19:45.060 --> 01:19:46.900
Use a air gun.

586
01:19:47.100 --> 01:19:52.140
Shoots out a little rock. about that far into the brain.
Sucks right back in. Animal never knows what hit him.

587
01:19:55.300 --> 01:19:58.660
- Why you telling me that. Sheriff?
- I don't know.

588
01:20:02.700 --> 01:20:04.820
My mind wanders.

589
01:21:27.860 --> 01:21:29.140
Hello. Carson.

590
01:21:32.260 --> 01:21:33.460
Let's go to your room.

591
01:21:46.220 --> 01:21:48.385
We don't have to do this.

592
01:21:48.420 --> 01:21:52.820
I'm a daytrader. I could just go home.

593
01:21:54.780 --> 01:21:56.100
Why would I let you do that?

594
01:21:56.380 --> 01:21:58.380
I'll make it worth your while.

595
01:21:58.420 --> 01:22:02.020
Take you to an ATM. Forteen grand in it.

596
01:22:02.140 --> 01:22:04.060
And everybody just walks away.

597
01:22:05.980 --> 01:22:07.740
An ATM...

598
01:22:11.940 --> 01:22:16.780
- I know where the satchel is.
- If you knew. you would have it with you.

599
01:22:17.460 --> 01:22:21.540
Find it from the river
bank. I know where it is.

600
01:22:22.780 --> 01:22:24.700
I know something better.

601
01:22:25.340 --> 01:22:27.380
- What's that?
- I know where it's going to be.

602
01:22:28.860 --> 01:22:35.380
- Where is that?
- It will be brought to me and placed at my feet.

603
01:22:36.820 --> 01:22:42.220
You don't know to a certainty.
Twenty minutes it could be here.

604
01:22:42.420 --> 01:22:46.580
I do know to a certainty. And you know
what's going to happen now. Carson?

605
01:22:47.660 --> 01:22:52.220
You should admit your situation.
There would be more dignity in it.

606
01:22:57.460 --> 01:22:58.860
You go to hell.

607
01:23:01.180 --> 01:23:02.420
Alright.

608
01:23:02.860 --> 01:23:04.220
Let me ask you something.

609
01:23:06.260 --> 01:23:11.180
If the rule you followed
brought you to this...

610
01:23:11.215 --> 01:23:13.620
...of what use was the rule?

611
01:23:19.220 --> 01:23:23.540
Do you have any idea how crazy you are?

612
01:23:24.620 --> 01:23:26.940
You mean the nature of this conversation?

613
01:23:27.300 --> 01:23:29.100
I mean the nature of you.

614
01:23:35.540 --> 01:23:39.740
You can have the money. Anton.

615
01:24:19.060 --> 01:24:20.360
<i>Hello?</i>

616
01:24:20.395 --> 01:24:21.660
Yes?

617
01:24:24.620 --> 01:24:26.420
<i>Is Carson Wells there?</i>

618
01:24:28.740 --> 01:24:30.940
Not in the sense that you mean.

619
01:24:33.260 --> 01:24:35.300
<i>You need to come see me.</i>

620
01:24:35.540 --> 01:24:37.180
Who is this?

621
01:24:37.660 --> 01:24:39.140
You know who it is.

622
01:24:40.420 --> 01:24:42.340
You need to talk to me.

623
01:24:42.580 --> 01:24:43.860
<i>I don't need to talk to you.</i>

624
01:24:43.895 --> 01:24:45.100
I think you do.

625
01:24:46.060 --> 01:24:48.260
Do you know where I'm going?

626
01:24:48.620 --> 01:24:50.780
Why would I care where you're going.

627
01:24:50.820 --> 01:24:52.820
I know where you are.

628
01:24:53.340 --> 01:24:55.380
<i>Yeah? Where am I?</i>

629
01:24:55.420 --> 01:24:57.460
You're in a hospital across the river.

630
01:24:57.500 --> 01:25:02.460
But that's not where I'm going.
Do you know where I'm going?

631
01:25:04.780 --> 01:25:06.420
<i>Yeah. I know where you're going.</i>

632
01:25:06.460 --> 01:25:08.020
Alright.

633
01:25:08.660 --> 01:25:10.505
<i>You know she won't be there.</i>

634
01:25:10.540 --> 01:25:12.740
It doesn't make any difference where she is.

635
01:25:12.780 --> 01:25:14.660
So what're you goin up there for?

636
01:25:18.740 --> 01:25:21.340
You know how this is going
to turn out. don't you?

637
01:25:23.100 --> 01:25:24.380
No.

638
01:25:25.500 --> 01:25:29.260
I think you do too. So
this is what I'll offer.

639
01:25:30.100 --> 01:25:32.580
You bring me the money and I'll let her go.

640
01:25:33.540 --> 01:25:37.340
<i>Otherwise she's accountable. Same as you.</i>

641
01:25:39.500 --> 01:25:41.860
That's the best deal you're going to get.

642
01:25:41.900 --> 01:25:46.100
I won't tell you you can save
yourself because you can't.

643
01:25:49.260 --> 01:25:51.420
Yeah. I'm goin to bring you somethin' alright.

644
01:25:52.660 --> 01:25:55.180
I've decided to make you
a special project of mine.

645
01:25:55.220 --> 01:25:57.180
You ain't goin' to have
to come look for me at all.

646
01:26:02.060 --> 01:26:04.060
- The motel in Del Rio?
- Yessir.

647
01:26:04.540 --> 01:26:06.580
None of the three had ID on 'em...

648
01:26:06.620 --> 01:26:08.460
...but they're tellin me
that all three is Mexicans.

649
01:26:09.140 --> 01:26:09.940
Was Mexicans.

650
01:26:10.100 --> 01:26:14.900
There's a question. Whether
they stopped it? And when?

651
01:26:16.900 --> 01:26:18.420
Yessir.

652
01:26:19.060 --> 01:26:21.500
Now. Wendell. did you inquire
about the lock cylinder?

653
01:26:21.540 --> 01:26:24.380
- Yessir. It was punched out.
- Okay.

654
01:26:25.620 --> 01:26:26.860
You wanna drive out there?

655
01:26:26.900 --> 01:26:30.900
No. that's all I've to look for and it sounds
like these old boys died of natural causes.

656
01:26:31.300 --> 01:26:32.345
How's that. Sheriff?

657
01:26:32.380 --> 01:26:34.620
Natural to the line of work they was in.

658
01:26:34.655 --> 01:26:35.620
Yessir.

659
01:26:35.660 --> 01:26:39.460
My god. Wendell. it's just all-out war.
I can't think of any other word for it.

660
01:26:39.500 --> 01:26:41.700
Who are these people?

661
01:26:41.940 --> 01:26:44.465
Here last week they found this couple out...

662
01:26:44.500 --> 01:26:47.100
...in California. they'd
rent out rooms to old people.

663
01:26:47.140 --> 01:26:51.780
Kill em. bury em in the yard and
cash their social security checks.

664
01:26:52.540 --> 01:26:56.220
They'd torture them first. I don't know why.

665
01:26:57.060 --> 01:26:59.540
Maybe their television set was broke.

666
01:26:59.860 --> 01:27:02.420
And this went on until. and here I quote:

667
01:27:03.700 --> 01:27:08.540
<i>Neighbors were alerted when a man ran from
the premises wearing only a dog collar.</i>

668
01:27:10.260 --> 01:27:13.860
You can't make up such a thing
as that. I dare you to even try.

669
01:27:13.900 --> 01:27:17.140
But that's what it took. you'll
notice. Get somebody's attention.

670
01:27:17.180 --> 01:27:20.420
Diggin graves in the back
yard didn't bring any.

671
01:27:27.500 --> 01:27:29.940
That's all right. I laugh myself sometimes.

672
01:27:32.460 --> 01:27:34.860
There ain't a whole lot else you can do.

673
01:27:37.340 --> 01:27:38.660
Tell me something.

674
01:27:39.060 --> 01:27:41.940
Who do you think gets through this
gate into the United States of America?

675
01:27:43.860 --> 01:27:46.420
I don't know. American citizens?

676
01:27:46.700 --> 01:27:49.060
Some American citizens.
Who do you think decides?

677
01:27:49.300 --> 01:27:52.540
- Well. you do. I reckon.
- That is correct. How do I decide?

678
01:27:53.420 --> 01:27:55.300
- I don't know.
- I ask questions.

679
01:27:55.340 --> 01:27:59.460
And if I get sensible answers then they get to go to
America. If I don't get sensible answers they don't.

680
01:27:59.500 --> 01:28:01.500
- Anything about that you don't understand?
- No sir.

681
01:28:01.540 --> 01:28:04.340
Then I ask you again. How you come
to be out here with no clothes?

682
01:28:05.780 --> 01:28:07.660
I got an overcoat on.

683
01:28:08.540 --> 01:28:10.340
- Are you jackin' with me?
- Oh. no sir.

684
01:28:10.380 --> 01:28:12.140
- Don't jack with me.
- Yes sir.

685
01:28:13.060 --> 01:28:15.340
- Are you in the service?
- No sir. I'm a veteran.

686
01:28:15.375 --> 01:28:17.740
- Nam?
- Yes sir. Two tours.

687
01:28:17.780 --> 01:28:18.940
What outfit?

688
01:28:18.980 --> 01:28:24.580
Twelfth Infantry Battalion.
August 7th 1966 to July 2nd 1968.

689
01:28:26.700 --> 01:28:28.420
- Wilson!
- Yessir.

690
01:28:30.340 --> 01:28:33.140
Get someone to help this man.
He needs to get into town.

691
01:28:42.300 --> 01:28:45.740
- How those Larries holdin' up?
- Oh. good.

692
01:28:45.780 --> 01:28:48.540
- I need everything else.
- Okay.

693
01:28:49.700 --> 01:28:52.260
You have a lot of people come
in here without any clothes on?

694
01:28:52.300 --> 01:28:54.660
No sir. it's unusual.

695
01:29:08.220 --> 01:29:09.580
<i>She don't want to talk to you.</i>

696
01:29:09.620 --> 01:29:10.940
Yes she does. Put her on.

697
01:29:10.980 --> 01:29:12.380
<i>Do you know what time it is?</i>

698
01:29:12.780 --> 01:29:15.060
I don't care what time it is.
And don't you hang up this phone.

699
01:29:20.340 --> 01:29:22.100
- Llewelyn.
- Hey you.

700
01:29:22.380 --> 01:29:25.340
- What should I do?
- You know what's goin' on?

701
01:29:25.580 --> 01:29:29.100
I don't know. I had the sheriff
here from Terrell County.

702
01:29:29.140 --> 01:29:30.500
What did you tell him?

703
01:29:30.700 --> 01:29:34.980
<i>What did I know to tell
him? You're hurt. ain't you?</i>

704
01:29:36.700 --> 01:29:38.500
What makes you say that?

705
01:29:38.900 --> 01:29:40.385
<i>I can hear it in your voice.</i>

706
01:29:40.420 --> 01:29:42.580
<i>There is falseness in his voice!</i>

707
01:29:42.900 --> 01:29:45.580
Look. I want you to meet me at
the Desert Sands motel in El Paso.

708
01:29:46.340 --> 01:29:48.820
Cause I'm gonna give you the
money and I'ma put you on a plane.

709
01:29:48.860 --> 01:29:51.425
Llewelyn. I ain't gonna
leave you in the lurch.

710
01:29:51.460 --> 01:29:55.380
No. This works better. With you gone and
I don't have the money. he can't touch me.

711
01:29:55.420 --> 01:29:57.345
But I can sure touch him.

712
01:29:57.380 --> 01:29:59.820
And after I find him I'll come and join you.

713
01:30:00.100 --> 01:30:03.460
<i>Find who? What am I
supposed to do with Mother?</i>

714
01:30:03.500 --> 01:30:05.660
- Nah. she'll be alright.
- She'll be alright?

715
01:30:05.700 --> 01:30:08.220
<i>Be all right?! I've got the cancer!</i>

716
01:30:08.260 --> 01:30:10.740
Ain't nobody's gonna bother her.

717
01:30:44.820 --> 01:30:46.020
Who are you?

718
01:30:50.580 --> 01:30:52.460
- Me?
- Yes.

719
01:30:52.500 --> 01:30:56.020
Nobody. Accounting.

720
01:30:58.020 --> 01:31:00.740
He gave the Mexicans a receiver.

721
01:31:02.900 --> 01:31:08.300
He feels... he felt that...
the more people looking...

722
01:31:08.340 --> 01:31:12.660
That's foolish. You pick the one right tool.

723
01:31:13.980 --> 01:31:19.500
I see. Are you going to shoot me?

724
01:31:25.740 --> 01:31:31.820
That depends. Do you see me?

725
01:31:34.860 --> 01:31:37.300
I always seen this is what it would come to.

726
01:31:37.580 --> 01:31:39.900
Three years ago I pre-visioned it.

727
01:31:40.140 --> 01:31:41.860
It ain't even three years we been married.

728
01:31:42.180 --> 01:31:46.260
Three years ago I said them
very words. No and Good.

729
01:31:46.460 --> 01:31:50.705
Here we are. Ninety degree heat.

730
01:31:50.740 --> 01:31:55.020
I got the cancer. And look at
this. Not even a home to go to.

731
01:31:55.820 --> 01:32:01.780
We're goin' to El Paso Texas. You know
how many people I know in El Paso Texas?

732
01:32:01.820 --> 01:32:05.140
- No ma'am.
- That's how many.

733
01:32:13.940 --> 01:32:17.020
- I didn't see my Prednizone.
- I put it in. Mama.

734
01:32:17.180 --> 01:32:20.540
- Well I didn't see it.
- Well. I put it in. That one.

735
01:32:20.980 --> 01:32:24.620
You just set there. I'll get
tickets and a cart for the bags.

736
01:32:25.020 --> 01:32:27.220
Do you need help with the bags. madam?

737
01:32:28.020 --> 01:32:30.900
Well. thank god there is one
gentleman left in West Texas.

738
01:32:31.180 --> 01:32:33.860
Yes. thank you. I am old and I am not well.

739
01:32:34.180 --> 01:32:38.420
- Which bus are you taking?
- We're going to El Paso. Don't ask me why.

740
01:32:38.700 --> 01:32:41.380
It's not often you see a Mexican in a suit.

741
01:32:41.700 --> 01:32:44.860
You go to El Paso? I know
it. Where are you staying?

742
01:32:45.620 --> 01:32:47.300
<i>Carla Jean. how are you?</i>

743
01:32:47.500 --> 01:32:51.380
Sheriff. was that a true
story about Charlie Walser?

744
01:32:51.580 --> 01:32:53.180
<i>Who's Charlie Walser?</i>

745
01:32:56.660 --> 01:33:00.780
True story? I couldn't swear to ever detail
but it's certainly true that it is a story.

746
01:33:01.620 --> 01:33:02.180
<i>Yeah. right.</i>

747
01:33:04.220 --> 01:33:06.220
Sheriff. can you give me
your word on somethin'?

748
01:33:06.340 --> 01:33:08.380
<i>Yes ma'am?</i>

749
01:33:08.780 --> 01:33:11.465
If I tell you where Llewelyn's headed...

750
01:33:11.500 --> 01:33:14.180
...you promise it'll be just
you goes and talks with him?

751
01:33:14.940 --> 01:33:16.220
You and nobody else.

752
01:33:16.540 --> 01:33:18.260
Yes ma'am. I do.

753
01:33:18.660 --> 01:33:20.700
<i>Llewelyn would never ask for help.</i>

754
01:33:21.140 --> 01:33:23.220
He never thinks he needs any.

755
01:33:23.460 --> 01:33:26.140
<i>Carla Jean. I will not harm your man.</i>

756
01:33:27.220 --> 01:33:30.820
<i>And he needs help. whether he knows it or not.</i>

757
01:33:39.660 --> 01:33:41.540
What's the problem there. neighbor?

758
01:33:42.900 --> 01:33:46.100
That'll suck some power. Over time.

759
01:33:48.020 --> 01:33:51.780
- You from around here?
- Alpine. Born and bred.

760
01:33:52.300 --> 01:33:52.900
Here ya go.

761
01:33:53.460 --> 01:33:58.660
- What airport would you use?
- Well? Airport or airstrip?

762
01:33:58.860 --> 01:34:02.060
- Airport.
- Well. where ya goin'?

763
01:34:02.980 --> 01:34:06.420
- I don't know.
- Just lightin' out for the territories. huh?

764
01:34:07.100 --> 01:34:09.020
Brother. I been there.

765
01:34:09.500 --> 01:34:09.980
Well...

766
01:34:10.620 --> 01:34:14.020
There's airstrips. The airport is El Paso.

767
01:34:14.940 --> 01:34:18.340
You want some place specific you might
could be better off just drivin' to Dallas.

768
01:34:19.220 --> 01:34:20.020
Not have to connect.

769
01:34:21.380 --> 01:34:25.980
- You gonna clamp them. buddy?
- Can you get those chicken crates out of the bed?

770
01:34:27.100 --> 01:34:29.100
What're you talkin' about?

771
01:34:45.100 --> 01:34:49.940
- Hey. Mr. Sporting Goods.
- Hey yourself.

772
01:34:51.020 --> 01:34:51.780
You a sport?

773
01:34:53.100 --> 01:34:54.980
Yeah. that's me.

774
01:34:55.540 --> 01:34:57.380
I got beers in my room.

775
01:34:59.500 --> 01:35:01.420
Waiting on my wife.

776
01:35:02.260 --> 01:35:06.620
- That's who you keep lookin' out the window for?
- Half.

777
01:35:06.660 --> 01:35:10.980
- What else then?
- Just lookin' for what's comin'.

778
01:35:12.420 --> 01:35:14.580
Yeah. but no one ever sees that.

779
01:35:15.620 --> 01:35:18.300
Beer. That's what's comin'.

780
01:35:19.020 --> 01:35:21.500
I'll bring the ice chest out
here. You can stay married.

781
01:35:21.540 --> 01:35:24.020
No ma'am. I know what beer leads to.

782
01:35:25.980 --> 01:35:28.300
Beer leads to more beer.

783
01:36:21.620 --> 01:36:23.700
Call police.

784
01:36:29.620 --> 01:36:31.180
Your local law enforcement.

785
01:36:33.620 --> 01:36:34.820
I'm not on their radio.

786
01:37:25.500 --> 01:37:28.220
Buy you a cup of coffee before you drive home?

787
01:37:28.820 --> 01:37:30.180
No money in his room there?

788
01:37:30.300 --> 01:37:34.820
Couple hundred on his person. Those
hombres would've taken the stash.

789
01:37:35.340 --> 01:37:39.420
I suppose so. Though they
was leavin' in a hurry.

790
01:37:39.780 --> 01:37:42.580
It's all the goddamned money. Ed Tom.

791
01:37:42.900 --> 01:37:44.620
The money and the drugs.

792
01:37:45.820 --> 01:37:48.860
It's just goddamned beyond everything.

793
01:37:49.340 --> 01:37:52.180
What's it mean? What's it leading to?

794
01:37:52.740 --> 01:37:57.340
You know. if you'd a told me twenty
years ago. I'd see children walking...

795
01:37:57.375 --> 01:38:01.940
the streets of our Texas towns with
green hair and bones in their noses.

796
01:38:02.740 --> 01:38:04.660
I just flat out wouldn't of believed you.

797
01:38:05.020 --> 01:38:08.820
Signs and wonders. But I think once
you quit hearin' sir and ma'am...

798
01:38:08.855 --> 01:38:10.700
...the rest is soon to follow.

799
01:38:11.220 --> 01:38:15.500
Oh. it's the tide. It's the dismal tide.

800
01:38:15.780 --> 01:38:18.140
- It is not the one thing.
- Not the one thing.

801
01:38:18.500 --> 01:38:20.260
None of that explains your man though.

802
01:38:21.380 --> 01:38:24.420
He's just a goddamn homicidal lunatic. Ed Tom.

803
01:38:24.660 --> 01:38:27.820
- I'm not sure he's a lunatic.
- Yeah well. what would you call him?

804
01:38:28.140 --> 01:38:31.820
I don't know. Sometimes I
think he's pretty much a ghost.

805
01:38:31.855 --> 01:38:33.700
- He's real all right.
- Oh yeah?

806
01:38:33.900 --> 01:38:37.780
All that at the? Motel.
It's beyond everything.

807
01:38:38.180 --> 01:38:40.420
Yeah. he has some hard bark on him.

808
01:38:41.060 --> 01:38:43.060
That don't hardly say it.

809
01:38:44.020 --> 01:38:45.865
He shoots the desk clerk one day.

810
01:38:45.900 --> 01:38:49.700
Walks right back in the next and
shoots a retired army colonel.

811
01:38:50.420 --> 01:38:51.940
It's hard to believe.

812
01:38:52.140 --> 01:38:55.020
Strolls right back into a crime scene.

813
01:38:55.380 --> 01:39:00.060
Who would do such a thing?
How do you defend against it?

814
01:39:02.460 --> 01:39:03.745
Good trip. Ed Tom.

815
01:39:03.780 --> 01:39:06.380
I'm sorry we couldn't help your boy.

816
01:42:38.540 --> 01:42:40.180
Min back!

817
01:42:40.460 --> 01:42:44.180
- How'd you know I was here?
- Who else'd be driving up your truck?

818
01:42:44.940 --> 01:42:46.580
- You heard it?
- How's that?

819
01:42:46.940 --> 01:42:52.900
- You heard what I'm - you havin fun
with me? - What give you that idea?

820
01:42:53.500 --> 01:42:56.700
- I seen one of the cats heard it. -
But - how'd you know it was my truck?

821
01:42:57.540 --> 01:43:00.420
I deduced it. When you walked in.

822
01:43:00.660 --> 01:43:02.260
How many of those things you got now?

823
01:43:02.300 --> 01:43:04.620
Cats? I don't know. Several.

824
01:43:05.340 --> 01:43:07.580
Well. it depends on what you mean by got.

825
01:43:08.380 --> 01:43:12.220
Some of 'em are half-wild. and
some of 'em are just outlaws.

826
01:43:15.740 --> 01:43:18.505
How you been. Ellis?

827
01:43:18.540 --> 01:43:24.140
You lookin' at it. I got
to say you lookin' older.

828
01:43:24.340 --> 01:43:25.820
I am older.

829
01:43:26.980 --> 01:43:29.265
Got a letter from your wife.

830
01:43:29.300 --> 01:43:33.980
She writes to me pretty regular.
keep me up on the family news.

831
01:43:34.620 --> 01:43:37.500
- Didn't know there was any.
- She told me you were quittin'.

832
01:43:40.700 --> 01:43:43.380
- You want a cup?
- 'Preciate it.

833
01:43:51.060 --> 01:43:52.780
How fresh is that coffee?

834
01:43:53.100 --> 01:43:58.460
I generally make a fresh pot ever
week even if there's some left over.

835
01:44:00.740 --> 01:44:03.940
That man who shot you died in prison.

836
01:44:05.300 --> 01:44:06.900
In Angola. Yeah.

837
01:44:07.620 --> 01:44:09.860
What would you a done if he'd been released?

838
01:44:10.700 --> 01:44:15.300
I don't know. Nothin.
Wouldn't be no point to it.

839
01:44:15.940 --> 01:44:18.540
I'm kindly surprised to hear you say that.

840
01:44:18.580 --> 01:44:22.105
Well. all the time you
spend tryin' to get back...

841
01:44:22.140 --> 01:44:25.700
...what's been took from you
more is goin' out the door.

842
01:44:26.100 --> 01:44:29.860
After a while. you just have to
try to get a tourniquet on it.

843
01:44:30.220 --> 01:44:34.060
Your granddaddy never asked
me to sign on as a deputy.

844
01:44:36.980 --> 01:44:39.540
Loretta tells me you're quittin'.

845
01:44:39.980 --> 01:44:41.540
How come're you doin' that?

846
01:44:41.820 --> 01:44:43.340
I don't know.

847
01:44:46.140 --> 01:44:48.460
I feel overmatched.

848
01:44:52.340 --> 01:44:54.700
I always figured when I got older...

849
01:44:55.300 --> 01:44:59.820
...God would sort of come
into my life in some way.

850
01:45:02.900 --> 01:45:04.380
He didn't.

851
01:45:07.780 --> 01:45:09.780
I don't blame him.

852
01:45:11.860 --> 01:45:15.260
If I was him I'd have the same
opinion about me that he does.

853
01:45:15.540 --> 01:45:17.620
You don't know what he thinks.

854
01:45:31.580 --> 01:45:35.700
I sent Uncle Mac's thumbbuster
and badge over to the Rangers.

855
01:45:35.735 --> 01:45:36.700
Put up in a museum.

856
01:45:38.100 --> 01:45:41.860
Your daddy ever tell you how
Uncle Mac come to his reward?

857
01:45:42.660 --> 01:45:46.340
Gunned down on his own porch
over in Hudspeth County.

858
01:45:48.580 --> 01:45:53.140
Seven or eight of 'em come up to
here. Wantin' this and wantin' that.

859
01:45:53.740 --> 01:45:56.620
Uncle Mac went back in the
house and got the shotgun...

860
01:45:56.655 --> 01:45:59.540
They was way ahead of him.

861
01:46:00.700 --> 01:46:02.860
Shot him in the doorway.

862
01:46:03.300 --> 01:46:06.140
Aunt Ella came out and
tried to stop the bleedin'.

863
01:46:06.180 --> 01:46:08.980
Uncle Mac all the while
tryin' to get that shotgun.

864
01:46:09.660 --> 01:46:13.540
They just sat there on their
horses watchin' him die.

865
01:46:15.180 --> 01:46:20.060
After a while. one of 'em says somethin
in Injun and they all turned and left out.

866
01:46:24.300 --> 01:46:28.140
Well. Uncle Mac knew the
score even if Aunt Ella didn't.

867
01:46:28.180 --> 01:46:30.540
Shot through the left lung.

868
01:46:31.420 --> 01:46:35.740
And that was that. As they say.

869
01:46:38.860 --> 01:46:44.580
- When did he die?
- 1909.

870
01:46:44.820 --> 01:46:50.620
No. I mean was it right away
or in the night or when was it?

871
01:46:50.820 --> 01:46:54.500
I believe it's that night. She
buried him the next mornin'.

872
01:46:55.140 --> 01:46:57.420
Diggin' in that hard old caliche.

873
01:47:00.980 --> 01:47:03.940
What you got ain't nothin new.

874
01:47:04.500 --> 01:47:07.500
This country is hard on people.

875
01:47:10.620 --> 01:47:13.380
You can't stop what's comin'.

876
01:47:14.700 --> 01:47:17.540
Ain't all waitin' on you.

877
01:47:19.700 --> 01:47:22.340
That's vanity.

878
01:48:22.380 --> 01:48:27.060
- I knew this wasn't done with.
- No.

879
01:48:27.740 --> 01:48:31.985
I ain't got the money.

880
01:48:32.020 --> 01:48:36.300
What little I had is long gone and
there's bills aplenty to pay yet.

881
01:48:37.820 --> 01:48:42.180
I buried my mother today. I
ain't paid for that neither.

882
01:48:43.220 --> 01:48:45.540
I wouldn't worry about it.

883
01:48:47.780 --> 01:48:50.180
I need to sit down.

884
01:49:04.780 --> 01:49:07.300
You got no cause to hurt me.

885
01:49:07.660 --> 01:49:11.100
No. But I gave my word.

886
01:49:11.980 --> 01:49:16.100
- You gave your word?
- To your husband.

887
01:49:18.700 --> 01:49:24.700
That don't make sense. You gave
your word to my husband to kill me?

888
01:49:24.980 --> 01:49:28.260
Your husband had the opportunity to save you.

889
01:49:28.295 --> 01:49:31.540
Instead. he used you to try to save himself.

890
01:49:36.540 --> 01:49:42.420
Not like that. Not like you say.

891
01:49:47.860 --> 01:49:49.740
You don't have to do this.

892
01:49:50.060 --> 01:49:51.780
They'll always say the same thing.

893
01:49:53.620 --> 01:49:55.540
What did they say?

894
01:49:55.940 --> 01:49:59.100
They say you don't have to do this.

895
01:49:59.500 --> 01:50:01.060
You don't.

896
01:50:09.540 --> 01:50:11.700
This is the best I can do.

897
01:50:12.820 --> 01:50:14.420
Call it.

898
01:50:18.860 --> 01:50:22.340
I knowed you was crazy when
I saw you sittin' there.

899
01:50:24.220 --> 01:50:27.340
I knowed exactly what was in store for me.

900
01:50:27.860 --> 01:50:30.380
- Call it.
- No.

901
01:50:31.820 --> 01:50:33.820
I ain't gonna call it.

902
01:50:37.260 --> 01:50:41.420
- Call it.
- The coin don't have no say.

903
01:50:41.940 --> 01:50:44.220
It's just you.

904
01:50:46.620 --> 01:50:50.100
Well. I got here the same way the coin did.

905
01:52:32.420 --> 01:52:35.580
Mister. there's a bone
stickin' out of your arm.

906
01:52:35.900 --> 01:52:37.780
I'm alright. Let me just sit here a minute.

907
01:52:38.100 --> 01:52:41.020
There's an ambulance comin'.
Man over yonder went to call.

908
01:52:41.260 --> 01:52:42.660
Alright.

909
01:52:43.340 --> 01:52:47.140
Are you all right? You got a
bone stickin' out of your arm.

910
01:52:48.140 --> 01:52:50.460
What will you take for that shirt?

911
01:52:55.420 --> 01:52:58.260
Hell mister. I'll give you my shirt.

912
01:53:05.340 --> 01:53:08.100
Look at that fuckin' bone.

913
01:53:08.300 --> 01:53:10.220
Tie this for me.

914
01:53:10.500 --> 01:53:12.340
Just tie it.

915
01:53:30.740 --> 01:53:35.300
Hell mister. Look. I don't mind helping
someone out. That's a lot of money.

916
01:53:35.340 --> 01:53:40.420
Take it. Take it and you didn't see me.

917
01:53:40.620 --> 01:53:42.140
I was already gone.

918
01:53:42.420 --> 01:53:44.020
Yessir.

919
01:53:48.340 --> 01:53:51.700
- Part of that's mine.
- You still got your damn shirt.

920
01:53:51.740 --> 01:53:55.220
- That ain't what it was for.
- Well maybe. but I'm still out a shirt.

921
01:54:16.540 --> 01:54:19.140
- Maybe I'll go ridin'.
- Okay.

922
01:54:19.340 --> 01:54:22.420
- What do you think?
- I can't plan your day.

923
01:54:24.300 --> 01:54:25.860
I mean. would you care to join me?

924
01:54:26.180 --> 01:54:28.060
Lord no. I'm not retired.

925
01:54:29.860 --> 01:54:32.220
Maybe I'll help out here then.

926
01:54:33.140 --> 01:54:34.820
Better not.

927
01:54:38.580 --> 01:54:42.100
- How'd you sleep?
- I don't know. Had dreams.

928
01:54:42.340 --> 01:54:45.700
Well you got time for 'em
now. Anything interesting?

929
01:54:46.420 --> 01:54:49.140
They always is to the party concerned.

930
01:54:51.620 --> 01:54:54.500
Ed Tom. I'll be polite.

931
01:54:57.700 --> 01:55:00.380
Okay. Two of 'em. Both had
my father. It's peculiar.

932
01:55:01.740 --> 01:55:05.780
I'm older now than he
ever was by twenty years.

933
01:55:05.820 --> 01:55:09.020
So. in a sense he's the younger man.

934
01:55:09.580 --> 01:55:11.825
Anyway. first one I don't
remember too well but...

935
01:55:11.860 --> 01:55:16.340
It was about meeting him in town
someplace where he gave me some money.

936
01:55:17.340 --> 01:55:19.140
I think I lost it.

937
01:55:20.980 --> 01:55:25.380
The second one. it was like we
was both back in older times...

938
01:55:26.020 --> 01:55:29.860
...and I was on horseback goin'
through the mountains of a night.

939
01:55:30.100 --> 01:55:33.420
Goin' through this pass in the mountains.

940
01:55:33.660 --> 01:55:42.300
It was cold and there's snow on the ground. He rode past me and
kept on goin'. Never said nothin goin' by. He just rode on past.

941
01:55:43.900 --> 01:55:48.020
He had his blanket wrapped
around him and his head down.

942
01:55:49.500 --> 01:55:51.540
When he rode past I seen he was...

943
01:55:51.575 --> 01:55:53.540
...carryin fire in a horn...

944
01:55:53.580 --> 01:55:57.900
...the way people used to do and I could
see the horn from the light inside of it.

945
01:55:58.140 --> 01:55:59.940
About the color of the moon.

946
01:56:01.460 --> 01:56:06.665
And in the dream I knew
that he was goin' on ahead...

947
01:56:06.700 --> 01:56:11.940
and that he's fixin to make a fire somewhere
out there in all that dark and all that cold.

948
01:56:15.620 --> 01:56:20.140
I knew that whenever I
got there he'd be there.

949
01:56:23.100 --> 01:56:24.220
Then. I woke up.

950
01:56:32.421 --> 01:56:35.421
Vtg
